Example of dynamic Roku content.

The other piece is the static BrightScript that builds the UI. This is packaged up and uploaded to Roku which creates the channel.

1. Become a Roku develop here: http://www.roku.com/developer

2. Download the SDK and the samples.

3. Some good tutorials: http://www.treygourley.com/2012/07/developing-a-basic-roku-channel/
						http://blog.defaultroute.com/2010/12/13/building-a-roku-channel-part-1/
